messages.subject: Re: Books...and "Jewelry & culture" :)
messages.messageBody:
<< Lakeland - not too far from you!! :) It may interest you to know that
Polk county is considered the hillbilly section of Florida, which may account
for my classy sense of humor.>>

ROFL I've lived in FL since 1973 (in Tampa, then here since 1978) and I know
whereof you speak :) We go up to Orlando every few weeks, it seems (just
last weekend we were there); maybe we can plan to stop by and see your new
toe ring the next time we're going that way!

And count me in on the "jewelry and culture" thing - I love jewelry, but odd,
funky stuff...BTW, there's a great little shop in Old Town, in Kissimmee,
that has some great stuff!

Linda in FL :) (who's certain that no one else is even remotely interested
in this conversation, and will take the rest of it off the list ...although
sharing books with Betsey, jewelry & culture, and learning while in the
Orlando area are certainly a part of OUR unschooling adventure ROFL)
